## 6. Zone Classification

For human readability, layers map to zones:

| Layers | Zone Name | Meaning |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| 0-1 | `chaos` | Unstructured; early sensing |
| 2 | `paradox` | Named but unresolved |
| 3 | `scar` | Stored, high-energy |
| 4 | `cooling` | Active processing |
| 5 | `draft_law` | Candidate principle |
| 6 | `canon` | Sealed, stable |

**Classification function:**

```python
def classify_zone(layer: int) -> str:
    if layer <= 1: return "chaos"
    if layer == 2: return "paradox"
    if layer == 3: return "scar"
    if layer == 4: return "cooling"
    if layer == 5: return "draft_law"
    return "canon"
```

