## 7. Eureka Detection

**Eureka** is the phase transition where a scar crosses into law territory.

**Definition:** Eureka occurs when:

```
layer_before < 5  AND  layer_after â‰¥ 5  AND  all_floors_pass
```

**Physics interpretation:**
- Cooling: `dE/dÏ„ < 0` (energy decreasing)
- Eureka: `dÂ²E/dÏ„Â² < 0` (acceleration of insight â€” curvature change)

**Detection in code:**

```python
def is_eureka(prev_layer: int, curr_layer: int, floors_pass: bool) -> bool:
    return prev_layer < 5 and curr_layer >= 5 and floors_pass
```

